               <msContents>
                  <summary>The content is not clear, but the general comic character is obvious enough. The storm (l. 4ff.) is an alegory (see l. 6), and the use of the highly poetical word "AHTES" points toward parody.  It offers little more than the second half of catalectic iambic tetrameters.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Location: Ann Arbor</note>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Recto; Verso published by G Schmeltz in I. Andorlini et al., Atti del XXII Congresso Internazionale di Papirologia, pp. 1202-1207.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
